Abyssinian:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Warm reddish-brown or ruddy coat with distinct ticked (agouti) pattern  
-Facial Features: Wedge-shaped head with slight nose break and defined cheekbones  
-Eye Shape and Color: Almond-shaped eyes; gold or green in color  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, slender, muscular body  
-Ear Shape and Position: Large, pointed ears set wide and forward  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, tapering tail matching body color  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Long, slim legs with small oval paws

American Bulldog:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Predominantly white coat often with patches of brindle, tan, or brown
-Facial Features: Broad, square-shaped head with pronounced muzzle and strong jaw
-Eye Shape and Color: Round eyes, typically dark brown or hazel
-Body Shape and Size: Large, muscular, and stocky build with deep chest
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized ears set high, usually rose or half-pricked
-Tail Shape and Length: Thick at base, tapering; typically medium length, carried low or straight
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong, sturdy legs with large round paws

American Pit Bull Terrier:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Short, smooth coat in various solid or mixed colors; often brindle, blue, fawn, or black
-Facial Features: Broad, flat skull with pronounced cheek muscles; strong, square jaw
-Eye Shape and Color: Round to almond-shaped eyes; colors range from brown to hazel
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, compact and muscular build with deep chest
-Ear Shape and Position: Ears set high; naturally rose-shaped or cropped to stand erect
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, tapering to a point; carried low or slightly curved
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Straight, strong legs with well-defined muscles; compact, round paws

Basset Hound:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Short, smooth coat; commonly tri-color (black, white, tan) or bi-color (lemon and white, red and white)
-Facial Features: Long, droopy muzzle with prominent nasal folds; loose, wrinkled skin around face
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, oval eyes; typically brown or hazel
-Body Shape and Size: Long, low-slung body with deep chest and broad ribcage; medium to large size but short height
-Ear Shape and Position: Very long, thick, floppy ears set low on head, hanging close to cheeks
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, slightly curved upward; thick at base tapering to tip
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Very short, stout legs with heavy bone structure; large, rounded paws with thick pads

Beagle:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Tri-color (black, white, and tan) or bi-color with large patches; short, smooth coat
-Facial Features: Broad skull, moderately squared muzzle, defined stop
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round eyes; brown or hazel
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, sturdy, medium-sized body with deep chest
-Ear Shape and Position: Long, floppy ears set low and close to head
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately long, carried high with slight curve, white tip often present
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Straight, strong legs; rounded paws with thick pads

Bengal:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Golden to orange coat with large rosettes and spots in black or dark brown; glittered sheen  
-Facial Features: Broad, wedge-shaped head with pronounced whisker pads and distinct “M” shape on forehead  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, almond-shaped eyes; vivid green, gold, or hazel  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium to large, muscular, athletic build  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small to medium, rounded ears set wide apart  
-Tail Shape and Length: Thick, medium-length tail with dark bands and solid black tip  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong legs with large, rounded paws often exhibiting spots or rosettes

Birman:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Cream or light-colored body with dark “point” coloration on face, ears, legs, and tail (seal, blue, chocolate, lilac points)
-Facial Features: Rounded face with distinct mask-like coloration on the muzzle and eyes
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round, deep sapphire blue eyes
-Body Shape and Size: Medium to large, sturdy and muscular with a balanced, rectangular body
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, rounded ears set wide apart and slightly tilted forward
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, bushy tail with point coloration matching the mask and legs
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Medium-length legs with white “gloves” on front paws and white “laces” on back paws, symmetrical and well-defined

Bombay:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Jet black, sleek, and short coat with a shiny, satin-like texture  
-Facial Features: Rounded, broad head with a short muzzle and pronounced whisker pads  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round eyes; vivid copper or deep gold color  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, muscular, and compact body  
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized ears, rounded tips, set wide apart and slightly forward  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, straight tail tapering to a rounded tip  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Medium-length legs with rounded, black paws

Boxer:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Short, smooth coat; fawn, brindle, or white; often with white chest and markings  
-Facial Features: Broad, square muzzle; pronounced stop; distinct underbite; black mask on face  
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark brown, medium-sized, expressive eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium to large, muscular, compact and athletic build  
-Ear Shape and Position: High-set ears, typically cropped or natural floppy  
-Tail Shape and Length: Short, docked or natural tapered tail  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Straight, strong legs; compact, well-arched paws with thick pads

British Shorthair:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Dense, plush coat; commonly solid blue-gray but also comes in other solid colors and bi-color patterns  
-Facial Features: Round, broad face with full cheeks and a short, broad nose  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round eyes; typically copper or deep gold, sometimes blue or green depending on coat color  
-Body Shape and Size: Cobby, muscular, and compact body with a broad chest  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small to medium-sized ears, rounded tips, set wide apart and slightly tilted forward  
-Tail Shape and Length: Thick, medium-length tail with a rounded tip  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Short, strong legs with large, round paws

Chihuahua:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Smooth or long coat; variety of solid colors or combinations including fawn, black, white, chocolate, and cream
-Facial Features: Rounded "apple" dome skull; short, slightly pointed muzzle
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round, expressive eyes; dark or lighter shades depending on coat color
-Body Shape and Size: Very small, compact, lightweight body; delicate bone structure
-Ear Shape and Position: Large, erect ears set at the side or top of the head, wide at base
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately long, curved or sickle-shaped tail, often carried over back or to the side
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Short, slender legs; small, dainty paws with arched toes

Egyptian Mau:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Silver, bronze, or smoke base with random, dark, distinct spots; contrast between spots and base color  
-Facial Features: M-shaped marking on forehead; dark-lined nose bridge; pronounced “worried” brow expression  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, almond-shaped, vivid green eyes with black “eyeliner” markings  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, muscular, and elegant with a slightly rounded belly  
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, pointed ears set slightly forward  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium-length tail with spots and a dark tip  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Medium-length legs with distinctive spots; hind legs longer than front legs; small, rounded paws

English Cocker Spaniel:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Medium-length, silky coat; variety of solid colors and parti-color patterns; feathering on legs and chest
-Facial Features: Broad muzzle with pronounced stop; defined eyebrows
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round, dark brown eyes
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, sturdy, medium-sized body with balanced proportions
-Ear Shape and Position: Long, low-set, pendulous ears densely feathered
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, traditionally docked, carried level or slightly elevated
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong, straight legs with well-feathered rear legs; compact, round paws

English Setter:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: White or light base coat with speckled or mottled orange, lemon, liver, or black "belton" spots  
-Facial Features: Long, narrow muzzle with pronounced stop and slightly tapered nose  
-Eye Shape and Color: Almond-shaped eyes, typically dark brown or hazel  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium to large, lean and athletic build with deep chest  
-Ear Shape and Position: Long, low-set ears, hanging close to head with feathered edges  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium-length tail, straight or slightly curved, with heavy feathering  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Long, straight legs with moderate feathering; oval, compact paws

German Shorthaired:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Short, dense coat; solid liver, liver and white, or liver and roan patterns; sometimes ticked or patched
-Facial Features: Broad skull with a pronounced stop; strong, square muzzle
-Eye Shape and Color: Almond-shaped eyes; colors range from dark brown to amber
-Body Shape and Size: Athletic, well-proportioned, lean but muscular body; medium to large size
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, broad at base, set high and fold forward close to head
-Tail Shape and Length: Usually docked short, straight tail; if natural, medium length and straight
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Long, strong legs; webbed feet with compact, rounded paws

Great Pyrenees:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Thick, dense double coat; predominantly white, sometimes with light tan or gray markings  
-Facial Features: Broad skull with strong muzzle; distinct black nose and lip edges  
-Eye Shape and Color: Almond-shaped eyes; dark brown color  
-Body Shape and Size: Large, powerful, muscular build with deep chest  
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, triangular ears set high and slightly rounded at tips, lying close to head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, heavily furred tail that hangs low and may curl upward at rest  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong, straight legs; large, rounded paws with well-arced toes and thick pads

Havanese:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Long, silky, often wavy or curly coat; colors vary widely including white, cream, black, brown, and combinations
-Facial Features: Rounded skull with moderately short muzzle; prominent stop
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, expressive, dark brown eyes; slightly oval shape
-Body Shape and Size: Small, sturdy, well-proportioned with slightly longer than tall build
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, drop ears set high and close to head, heavily feathered
-Tail Shape and Length: Tail carried high and curved over back; heavily plumed
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Medium-length legs with feathered fur; small, compact, rounded paws

Japanese Chin:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Predominantly white coat with black or red patches, silky texture  
-Facial Features: Flat, broad face with a short, pushed-in nose (brachycephalic)  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round, dark eyes set wide apart  
-Body Shape and Size: Small, compact, and slightly square body  
-Ear Shape and Position: Feathered, heart-shaped ears set high and wide on the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Plumed tail carried over the back in a graceful curve  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Short legs with feathered fur and small, dainty paws

Keeshond:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Thick double coat, gray and black mixed with cream and silver shading; distinct "spectacles" markings around eyes  
-Facial Features: Fox-like face with strong muzzle; pronounced black mask and facial markings  
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark brown, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, sturdy, compact body with a deep chest  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small to medium, triangular, erect ears set high on head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Plumed tail curled tightly over back  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Straight, medium-length legs with rounded, compact paws covered in dense fur

Leonberger:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Thick double coat, lion-like mane, golden-yellow to reddish-brown with black mask
-Facial Features: Broad head with pronounced black mask covering muzzle and around eyes
-Eye Shape and Color: Medium-sized, almond-shaped eyes; dark brown color
-Body Shape and Size: Large, muscular, and balanced; substantial weight and height
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, pendant ears set high and close to head
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, bushy tail carried low or slightly curved upwards
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong, muscular legs with large, round, well-padded paws

Maine Coon:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Long, shaggy fur; variety of colors and patterns including tabby, tortoiseshell, and solid  
-Facial Features: Square muzzle with prominent whisker pads; high cheekbones  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, slightly oval eyes; green, gold, or copper tones  
-Body Shape and Size: Large, muscular, rectangular body; broad chest  
-Ear Shape and Position: Large, wide-based ears with lynx-like tufts at tips; set high on head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, bushy tail, tapering  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong, sturdy legs; large, tufted paws adapted for snow walking

Miniature Pinscher:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Smooth, short coat; commonly black and rust, chocolate and rust, or solid red
-Facial Features: Narrow, pointed muzzle with distinct stop; defined jawline
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark, oval-shaped eyes with keen, alert expression
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, well-balanced, muscular body; small stature (10-12.5 inches tall)
-Ear Shape and Position: Erect, pointed ears often cropped or natural; set high on head
-Tail Shape and Length: Short, straight tail usually docked; set high
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Slim, straight legs; small, compact feet with arched toes

Newfoundland:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Thick double coat, predominantly black, brown, or Landseer (white with black markings)  
-Facial Features: Broad skull with pronounced stop, large muzzle, often a gentle expression  
-Eye Shape and Color: Medium-sized, deep-set, dark brown eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Large, massive, muscular build with broad chest and strong frame  
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, triangular, set well back and close to head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, heavily feathered tail carried low or gently curved  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong, straight legs with large, webbed paws suitable for swimming

Persian:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Long, dense, and flowing coat; solid, shaded, or bi-color patterns common  
-Facial Features: Extremely flat, broad face with pushed-in nose (brachycephalic)  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round eyes; vivid copper, blue, or green depending on coat color  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium to large, cobby (stocky and compact) body with broad chest  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small, rounded ears set low and wide apart, often tufted  
-Tail Shape and Length: Short, bushy tail carried low  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Short, thick legs with large, round, tufted paws

Pomeranian:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Dense, double coat; common colors include orange, black, cream, sable, and parti-color  
-Facial Features: Fox-like face with a short, tapered muzzle and pronounced stop  
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, small, sturdy body; typically 3-7 pounds  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small, erect, triangular ears set high on the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Plumed tail, heavily furred, carried high and curled over the back  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Short legs with small, dainty, rounded paws

Pug:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Typically fawn, apricot, or black with smooth short coat; distinct black muzzle mask
-Facial Features: Pronounced wrinkled forehead, flat broad face, short snout (brachycephalic)
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, round, dark eyes set wide apart
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, square-shaped, muscular, small to medium size
-Ear Shape and Position: Small, thin, folded ears (rose or button) positioned high on head
-Tail Shape and Length: Curled tightly over hip in a double curl
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Short, sturdy legs with small, thick paws

Ragdoll:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Semi-longhair with colorpoint patterns (seal, blue, chocolate, lilac, flame, cream)  
-Facial Features: Rounded head with a flat plane, distinct mask covering the nose and cheeks  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, oval-shaped, vivid blue eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Large, muscular, and heavy-bodied with rectangular shape  
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, rounded tips, set wide apart with slight tilt forward  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, bushy tail proportional to body length  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Medium-length legs with large, tufted paws

Russian Blue:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Solid blue-gray coat with a dense, double-layered texture and silvery sheen
-Facial Features: Broad, wedge-shaped head with a straight nose and prominent whisker pads
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, almond-shaped eyes; vivid green color
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, slender, and muscular body with graceful posture
-Ear Shape and Position: Large, pointed ears set high and wide apart
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium-length, tapering tail proportional to body
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Long, slender legs with small, oval paws matching fur color

Saint Bernard:
-Fur Color and Pattern: White base with large reddish-brown patches, often around back and sides; some black shading on face
-Facial Features: Broad, large head with prominent stop; distinctive black mask around eyes and muzzle; loose skin folds around face
-Eye Shape and Color: Medium-sized, deep-set eyes; dark brown color
-Body Shape and Size: Very large, heavy, muscular build with deep chest and broad shoulders
-Ear Shape and Position: Medium-sized, triangular, floppy ears set high and close to head
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, bushy tail, carried low or slightly curved
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Thick, strong legs; large, rounded paws with well-arched toes and substantial pads

Samoyed:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Pure white or cream, dense double coat, fluffy texture  
-Facial Features: Broad, smiling expression ("Sammy smile"), black nose  
-Eye Shape and Color: Almond-shaped, dark brown eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium to large, sturdy and muscular build  
-Ear Shape and Position: Erect, triangular ears, set high on the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Plumed tail, carried curled over the back  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong legs, compact, well-padded, furry paws

Scottish Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Dense, wiry coat; predominantly black, brindle, or wheaten  
-Facial Features: Distinctive long beard and eyebrows; rectangular muzzle  
-Eye Shape and Color: Small, dark, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, sturdy, low-set body; short-legged  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small, erect, pointed ears set high on the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Straight, moderately short tail carried upright  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Short, strong legs with large, rounded paws

Shiba Inu:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Red, sesame (red with black-tipped hairs), black-and-tan, or cream; double coat with soft undercoat and stiff outer coat  
-Facial Features: Fox-like face with distinct white “urajiro” markings on cheeks, chest, and muzzle  
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark brown, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, muscular, well-proportioned body; small to medium size  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small, triangular, erect ears set high on the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Thick, curled tail carried over the back  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Straight, sturdy legs; small, cat-like, well-arched paws

Siamese:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Cream or pale body with dark “points” on face, ears, paws, and tail (seal, chocolate, blue, or lilac)
-Facial Features: Long, narrow wedge-shaped head with prominent muzzle and straight nose
-Eye Shape and Color: Almond-shaped, vivid cobalt blue eyes
-Body Shape and Size: Slender, elongated, and muscular body with fine bones
-Ear Shape and Position: Large, pointed ears set wide and high on head
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, thin, tapering tail matching point color
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Long, slim legs with small oval paws, darker color matching points

Sphynx:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Mostly hairless skin, can show pigmentation patterns, often appearing wrinkled  
-Facial Features: Prominent cheekbones, pronounced whisker pads, broad nose with slight break  
-Eye Shape and Color: Large, lemon-shaped eyes; diverse colors including green, blue, or gold  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, muscular, sturdy body with visible musculature  
-Ear Shape and Position: Very large, wide-based ears set high on the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, slender, tapering tail, often described as whip-like  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Long, slender legs with thick, cushiony pads on paws, noticeable toes due to lack of fur

Staffordshire Bull Terrier:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Short, smooth coat in solid colors or bi-color; common colors include brindle, black, blue, fawn, red, or white
-Facial Features: Broad, short muzzle with pronounced cheek muscles; strong jaw; distinct stop between forehead and nose
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark, round eyes set low and wide apart
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, muscular, medium-sized body with a deep chest and broad shoulders
-Ear Shape and Position: Rose or half-prick ears set high on the head
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium-length, tapering tail carried low and straight
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Strong, muscular legs with round, compact paws

Wheaten Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Soft, wavy, pale wheaten (light beige to golden) coat, uniform color without markings  
-Facial Features: Broad, rectangular muzzle with pronounced whiskers and beard  
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark, almond-shaped eyes with a friendly, alert expression  
-Body Shape and Size: Medium-sized, sturdy, square-proportioned body with strong bone structure  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small to medium, triangular ears set high and fold forward close to the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately short, carried upright or slightly curved  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Straight, well-boned legs with compact, round paws covered in soft fur

Yorkshire Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Steel blue body coat with rich tan on head, chest, and legs  
-Facial Features: Small, flat skull with a short muzzle and black nose  
-Eye Shape and Color: Dark, medium-sized, round eyes with a bright, alert expression  
-Body Shape and Size: Compact, small, well-proportioned body with a straight back  
-Ear Shape and Position: Small, V-shaped ears, carried erect and set high on the head  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, carried slightly higher than the level of the back  
-Legs and Paws Characteristics: Straight, fine boned legs with small, rounded paws
